http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Beginning Vocal Music II Curriculum Framework

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Beginning Vocal Music I-IV are two-semester courses designed for traditional and emerging ensembles. Vocal music students will demonstrate an ability to apply music fundamentals and vocal techniques in the production, performance, analysis, and critique of vocal music performance. Students are expected to apply sight-reading skills, improvisational skills, and performance techniques in solo, small group, and large group settings. Vocal music students will critique vocal music performances and deeply reflect upon the impact of vocal music on society, as well as societal influences on vocal music. Students will regularly perform vocally in a variety of settings and will demonstrate successful completion of vocal music student learning expectations.
Creating
Students will generate and conceptualize artistic ideas and work.
Improvise rhythms, melodies, and/or accompaniments
Students will organize and develop artistic ideas and work.
Identify notes written on lines, in spaces, and on ledger lines of treble clef and bass clef

Notate melodic or rhythmic ideas or motifs, using standard notation or digital recording
  • 2/4 and 6/8 time signatures
  • pattern of a dotted quarter note followed by an eighth note or eighth rest
Compose a four-measure phrase with accompaniment
Create movement that reflects musical form
Students will refine and complete artistic work.
Refine draft compositions, using collaboratively-generated criteria
Share personally-developed motifs that demonstrate understanding of elements of music as an ensemble

Students will analyze, interpret, and select artistic work for presentation.
Explore a variety of vocal repertoire in two-part harmony at an appropriate level of difficulty

Demonstrate sight-reading skills by singing with others
  • 4/4 time
  • quarter notes, half notes, whole notes, and quarter rests

Identify musical timbre
  • brass
  • electronic
  • percussion
  • string
  • vocal

  • two-part

Students will develop and refine artistic work for presentation.

Connecting

The student will relate artistic ideas and works with societal, cultural, and historical context to deepen understanding.
